Source: bcad
Section: electronics
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jason Brillante <jason@efrits.fr>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), liblapin-dev
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://hangedbunnystudio.com/

Package: bcad
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, libbcad0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: BunnyCAD circuit simulator and editor
 BunnyCAD is a digital circuit editor and simulator used as a reference oracle
 for RED Spice / Nanotekspice-style circuit exercises.
 .
 This package installs the bcad frontend and creates /usr/share/bcad, the
 default directory intended for external BunnyCAD components.

Package: libbcad0
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: BunnyCAD circuit simulation shared library
 This package contains the shared library used by BunnyCAD and by external
 tools that need to load or simulate BunnyCAD circuits.

Package: libbcad-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, libbcad0 (= ${binary:Version}), liblapin-dev
Description: development files for BunnyCAD components and evaluators
 This package contains the BunnyCAD headers, static archive, shared-library
 linker symlink and pkg-config file. It is intended for developing external
 .so components and Scolaire/Evaluator integrations using libbcad.
